    TEXT_LINE: "An array object represents a multidimensional, homogeneous array"@83..147
    NEWLINE: "\n"@147..148
    TEXT_LINE: "of fixed-size items.  An associated data-type object describes the"@148..214
    NEWLINE: "\n"@214..215
    TEXT_LINE: "format of each element in the array (its byte-order, how many bytes it"@215..285
    NEWLINE: "\n"@285..286
    TEXT_LINE: "occupies in memory, whether it is an integer, a floating point number,"@286..356
    NEWLINE: "\n"@356..357
    TEXT_LINE: "or something else, etc.)"@357..381
    NEWLINE: "\n"@381..382
    BLANK_LINE: "\n"@382..383
    TEXT_LINE: "Arrays should be constructed using `array`, `zeros` or `empty` (refer"@383..452
    NEWLINE: "\n"@452..453
    TEXT_LINE: "to the See Also section below).  The parameters given here refer to"@453..520
    NEWLINE: "\n"@520..521
    TEXT_LINE: "a low-level method (`ndarray(...)`) for instantiating an array."@521..584
    NEWLINE: "\n"@584..585
    BLANK_LINE: "\n"@585..586
    TEXT_LINE: "For more information, refer to the `numpy` module and examine the"@586..651
    NEWLINE: "\n"@651..652
    TEXT_LINE: "methods and attributes of an array."@652..687
  }
